Beans are a great source of fiber. That’s vital because most Americans don’t get the proposed 25 to 38 grams each day. Fiber helps keep you normal and seems to preserve you against heart disease, high cholesterol, high blood pressure, and digestive illness.

According to WebMD, an article Reviewed by Christine Mikstas, RD, LD stated that eating beans and legumes daily as part of a healthy eating plan can help lower blood cholesterol and triglyceride levels, as well as stabilize blood sugar levels. However, in this article, I will list out some health benefits of consuming beans regularly.
1. Free from Heart Attack
Regular Consumption of beans aid in resisting Conditions like heart attack, you can only favor your ticker by consuming beans regularly as your diet. It’s medically proven that regular eating of beans helps to lower your LDL “bad” cholesterol. For a heart-healthy food option, try a simple salad made from beets, beans, and greens.
2. Prevent you from Diabetes attack
If you are the type that consumes excess carbs which is responsible for Causing diabetes, then you ought to add beans into your diet in other to prevent you from Diabetes attacks. Not just that, it also helps control the high blood sugar which causes symptoms of the disease. Steam some fresh green beans with a sprinkle of salt and a touch of olive oil for a delicious summer side dish.
3. Cancer
Its medically proven that beans contain Antioxidants and Anti-inflammatory substances, the presence of this nutrient is Capable to reduce the risk of contracting cancer in the body system. In particular, brown beans are recommended because they are high in antioxidants to prevent cancer cell proliferation in the body


